quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  12,104,Thou askest of them no wage for it; it is nothing but a reminder unto all beings
  12,105,"How many a sign there is in the heavens and in the earth that they pass by, turning away from it"
  12,106,"And the most part of them believe not in God, but they associate other gods with Him"
  12,107,"Do they feel secure that there shall come upon them no enveloping of the chastisement of God, or that the Hour shall not come upon them suddenly when they are unaware"
  12,108,"Say: 'This is my way. I call to God with sure knowledge, I and whoever follows after me. To God be glory! And I am not among the idolaters"
  12,109,"We sent not forth any before thee, but men We revealed to of the people living in the cities. Have they not journeyed in the land? Have they not beheld how was the end of those before them?. Surely the abode of the world to come is better for those that are godfearing. What, do you not understand"
  12,110,"Till, when the Messengers despaired, deeming they were counted liars, Our help came to them and whosoever We willed was delivered. Our might will never be turned back from the people of the sinners"
  12,111,"In their stories is surely a lesson to men possessed of minds; it is not a tale forged, but a confirmation of what is before it, and a distinguishing of every thing, and a guidance, and a mercy to a people who believe"